                <head>204. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On May 29 the United States and Indonesia concluded an agreement under Title I of
                    Public Law 480 by which the United States agreed to provide Indonesia with
                    approximately $40.3 million of wheat, cotton, rice, and nonfat dry powdered
                    milk. The agreement, which was signed in Djakarta by Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_JHP1">Jones</persName> and Acting Foreign Minister Hardi,
                    entered into force that same day; for text, see 10 <gloss target="#t_UST1"
                        >UST</gloss> 1079. Documentation on the negotiations leading up to the
                    agreement is in Department of State, Central File 411.56D41.</p>
            </div>
